Cell.Data: The state of the condition such as whether it is active, inactive, or resolved
Whether the problem was a factor in death
Whether the problem was the cause or factor in the subject's death. Applicable only to deceased patients.
What is the value set for this? Agreed to cut this with CIMI and Claude since it isn't clear how cause of death will be modeled.

Characterizes potential impact of the condition on life, durable physiological function, or quality of life. May include concepts such as self-resolving, life-threatening, requires hospitalization, or potential loss of function or capacity. Different from severity in that a moderate subarachnoid hemorrhage is likely to be highly critical, whereas a moderate headache is not as important.
What is the value set for this?
Further conditions, problems, diagnoses, procedures or events or the substance that caused/triggered this Condition
Although a condition may be caused by a substance, this is not intended to be used to record allergies/adverse reactions to substances
Further conditions, problems, diagnoses, procedures or events or the substance that preceded this Condition

A result of the condition. The "Cause of death" for a patient is typically captured as an Observation. The "outcome" doesn't imply causality. Some outcomes might not be assessable until the condition.clinicalStatus is no longer active.
Conditions ruled out for this condition
Identifies what potential diagnoses have been ruled out for this condition
Allow linking a Condition (generally one representing a set of symptoms where no firm diagnosis exists yet) to another Condition that is marked as "ruled out"
This condition has an unspecified relationship with another condition.
When the relationship is specified, use the more specific extension, such as condition-dueTo, condition-occurredFollowing, or condition-part of.
Date the condition was first asserted
The date on which the existence of the Condition was first asserted or acknowledged
The assertedDate is in the context of the recording practitioner and might not be the same as the recordedDate
The clinical course of the disease
The clinical course of the disease (how the disease behaves over time), such as acute versus chronic.
